# ðŸ§© Part 3 â€” Practical Coding Exercises for Data Scientist

### 1. Normalize an array (min-max).

```python
(arr - arr.min()) / (arr.max() - arr.min())
```

### 2. Standardize an array (z-score).

```python
(arr - arr.mean()) / arr.std()
```

### 3. Replace NaN values with 0.

```python
np.nan_to_num(arr, nan=0)
```

### 4. Extract even numbers.

```python
arr[arr % 2 == 0]
```

### 5. Create identity matrix.

```python
np.eye(4)
```

### 6. Compute dot product of two vectors.

```python
np.dot(a, b)
```

### 7. Compute Euclidean distance between two points.

```python
np.linalg.norm(a - b)
```

### 8. Get top 3 largest values.

```python
arr[np.argsort(arr)][-3:]
```

### 9. Remove outliers using IQR.

```python
q1, q3 = np.percentile(arr, [25,75])
iqr = q3 - q1
clean = arr[(arr >= q1 - 1.5*iqr) & (arr <= q3 + 1.5*iqr)]
```

### 10. Build a confusion matrix manually.

```python
mat = np.zeros((n_classes, n_classes), int)
for t, p in zip(y_true, y_pred):
    mat[t][p] += 1
```

